(40, 20, 7, 40, 22, 9, 10, 'Go ye also into the vineyard', 'Invitation to the Vineyard and Wedding', 'This connection highlights the theme of invitation to labor and fellowship. Both passages emphasize the call to gather those who are uninvited or overlooked, whether to work in the vineyard or to attend the wedding.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 7, 42, 14, 21, 23, 'whatsoever is right, that shall ye receive', 'Invitation to the Uninvited', 'This connection highlights the theme of inviting those who are overlooked or marginalized. Both passages emphasize the call to bring in those who have not been hired or are not initially included.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 7, 43, 9, 4, 4, 'Go ye also into the vineyard', 'Work in the Vineyard', 'This connection highlights the theme of labor and urgency in both passages. In Matthew, the call to work in the vineyard reflects the need for laborers, while John emphasizes the necessity of working while there is time.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 7, 44, 4, 16, 16, 'whatsoever is right, that shall ye receive', 'Response to Divine Action', 'This connection highlights the theme of responding to a call or action from God. In Matthew, the workers are invited to the vineyard, while in Acts, the leaders are confronted with a notable miracle that demands a response.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 8, 5, 24, 15, 15, 'give them their hire', 'Connection of Labor and Payment', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of timely payment for labor. Matthew 20:8''s instruction to give hire ''from the last unto the first'' reflects the urgency found in Deuteronomy 24:15''s command to pay laborers by day''s end.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 8, 45, 2, 6, 10, 'give them their hire', 'Divine Justice and Reward', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine justice in both passages, where rewards are given according to one''s deeds. Matthew emphasizes the order of payment, while Romans discusses rendering to every man according to his deeds.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 8, 60, 4, 10, 10, NULL, 'Stewardship and Grace', 'This connection highlights the theme of stewardship in both passages. In Matthew, the steward is tasked with distributing wages, while 1 Peter emphasizes being good stewards of God''s grace.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 8, 1, 15, 2, 2, 'steward', 'Connection of Stewardship', 'This connection highlights the role of a steward in both passages. In Matthew, the steward distributes wages, while in Genesis, Abram refers to Eliezer as the steward of his house, indicating a theme of stewardship and responsibility.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 8, 1, 39, 4, 6, NULL, 'Overseer and Stewardship Connection', 'This connection highlights the role of stewardship in both passages. In Matthew, the steward is tasked with distributing wages, while in Genesis, Joseph is made overseer of the Egyptian''s house, managing all that he has.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 8, 3, 19, 13, 13, NULL, 'Wages and Fairness in Labor', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of timely payment for labor. Matthew 20:8 highlights the order of payment, while Leviticus 19:13 stresses that wages should not be withheld overnight.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 8, 40, 13, 39, 40, 'give them their hire', 'Harvest and Reaping Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of reaping and the order of judgment. Both passages emphasize the process of gathering, whether it be laborers receiving their hire or the reapers gathering at the end of the world.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 9, 40, 20, 2, 2, 'a penny', 'Laborers'' Payment Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the payment of ''a penny'' for labor. The first verse illustrates the payment received by those hired last, while the second verse establishes the agreed wage for all laborers.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 9, 42, 23, 40, 43, NULL, 'Grace and Reward in Salvation', 'This connection highlights the theme of unexpected grace and reward. In both passages, individuals receive a generous reward despite their circumstances, emphasizing God''s mercy and the promise of paradise.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 9, 45, 4, 3, 6, 'received every man a penny', 'Grace and Reward in Faith', 'This connection highlights the theme of grace in both passages. In Matthew, those hired last receive equal reward, illustrating grace, while Romans emphasizes that righteousness is counted through faith, not works, suggesting a similar principle of unmerited favor.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 9, 49, 1, 6, 8, NULL, 'Grace and Acceptance in Christ', 'This connection highlights the theme of grace in both passages. In Matthew, the workers receive their wages despite working less, reflecting God''s unmerited favor, which is echoed in Ephesians where believers are accepted through grace.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 9, 49, 2, 8, 10, NULL, 'Grace and Reward Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of grace in both passages. In Matthew 20:9, the workers receive a penny regardless of their labor, reflecting God''s unmerited favor, while Ephesians 2:8 emphasizes salvation as a gift, not earned by works.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 9, 45, 5, 20, 21, 'received every man a penny', 'Grace and Reward Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of grace in both passages. In Matthew, those hired last receive a full reward, paralleling how Romans emphasizes that grace abounds even where sin increases.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 9, 54, 1, 14, 16, NULL, 'Grace and Mercy in Salvation', 'This connection highlights the theme of grace and mercy in both passages. In Matthew, those hired last receive a full wage, symbolizing God''s generous grace, while in 1 Timothy, Paul speaks of obtaining mercy as the chief of sinners, illustrating the abundant grace offered to all.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 11, 42, 19, 7, 7, 'murmured', 'Murmuring Against Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of murmuring against authority figures. In Matthew, the workers complain about the householder''s decisions, while in Luke, the crowd murmurs about Jesus associating with a sinner.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 11, 52, 2, 16, 16, 'murmured against the goodman of the house', 'Response to Injustice', 'Both passages emphasize a reaction to perceived injustice. In Matthew, the murmuring reflects dissatisfaction with the goodman's decisions, while in 1 Thessalonians, the forbidding of the Gentiles indicates a similar grievance against those who oppose salvation.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 11, 42, 5, 30, 30, 'murmured', 'Murmuring Against Authority', 'This connection highlights the theme of murmuring against authority figures. Both passages depict individuals expressing dissatisfaction or complaint, whether against the goodman of the house or Jesus'' association with publicans and sinners.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 11, 44, 11, 2, 3, 'murmured against the goodman of the house', 'Murmuring and Contention', 'This connection highlights the theme of discontent among groups regarding actions taken by others. Both passages emphasize a reaction of murmuring or contention against perceived injustices or breaches of norms.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 11, 44, 13, 45, 45, 'murmured against the goodman of the house', 'Envy and Murmuring', 'This connection highlights the theme of discontent and envy in both passages. In Matthew, the murmuring reflects dissatisfaction with the goodman of the house, while in Acts, the Jews express envy and contradict Paul.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 11, 65, 1, 16, 16, 'murmured against the goodman of the house', 'Murmuring and Complaining Theme', 'This connection highlights the theme of murmuring and complaining present in both passages. In Matthew, the workers murmur against the goodman of the house, while Jude describes individuals as murmurers and complainers.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 12, 45, 11, 5, 6, 'made them equal unto us', 'Grace and Equal Treatment', 'This connection highlights the theme of grace and equality in God''s treatment of individuals. Both passages emphasize that worthiness is not based on works or effort, but rather on grace, suggesting that all are treated equally regardless of their labor.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 12, 42, 12, 55, 55, 'heat of the day', 'Heat and Labor Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of heat, with Matthew referring to the ''burden and heat of the day'' and Luke mentioning ''the heat'' that follows the south wind. This connection highlights the physical and metaphorical implications of heat in relation to labor and expectation.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 12, 42, 14, 10, 11, NULL, 'Humility and Exaltation Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of humility and the reversal of social status. In Matthew, those who worked longer feel entitled, while in Luke, the humble are exalted. This connection highlights the value of humility over self-exaltation.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 12, 47, 11, 23, 28, 'borne the burden and heat of the day', 'Labor and Suffering Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of labor and the burdens borne by individuals. In Matthew, the workers express frustration over equal treatment despite differing efforts, while in 2 Corinthians, Paul lists his extensive sufferings and labors for Christ, highlighting the weight of his ministry.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 12, 23, 58, 2, 3, 'made them equal unto us', 'Equality and Justice in Labor', 'Both passages emphasize the disparity in reward and the expectations of justice. In Matthew, the workers express frustration over perceived inequality, while in Isaiah, the people question God''s recognition of their efforts and righteousness.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 20, 12, 32, 4, 8, 8, 'burden and heat of the day', 'Burden and Heat Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the experience of suffering and the desire for relief. In Matthew, the ''burden and heat of the day'' reflects the toil of labor, while Jonah''s fainting under the sun illustrates personal distress.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
